    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>
                <hi rend="underline">
                    <add>Yiddish</add>
                </hi>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(10)"><placeName>New York</placeName>, <date>Monday</date>,</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)"><date>25th of Sivan(June) 1862</date>.</p>
            <p>To my dear friend, <addressee>Lippman Leeser</addressee>,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Friend:</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">God is my help, the Creator of heaven, and He<lb/>* who made the
                land from the formless void, that I<lb/> have heard no voice which aroused me
                against my<lb/> friend. Is this just and right?</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">For several months past I have been more<lb/> upset than ever
                because of the unpleasant ex<lb/>perience which I had through
                    <persName>Ettinger</persName>. The order<lb/> of these sad events through which
                I am delayed<lb/> in completing my work, or to undertake any-<lb/>thing new, so as
                to be able to support myself upset<lb/> and bewilder me. “A man is born for
                trouble”.*<lb/> But not for this kind of trouble. I deal with<lb/> general and
                Jewish books and stationary, but<lb/> the <add>blank</add> have forsaken me.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">And now, dear friend, after long pain<lb/> and delay (for my prayer
                has been heard) I am<lb/> almost finished with the work in Hebrew “Your
                    Nati<add>?</add> me<lb/> Hagvei <add>?</add> Ha-Selang<add>?</add>” (My dove
                from the nests of the Rock)<lb/> Cantides 214<lb/> Now, I beg of you to let me know
                whether I ought<lb/> to let it be copied for me in square letters, that<lb/> would
                cost too much. Rashi script would cost less<lb/> It were even better if you or
                someone else over</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">*From <persName>Job</persName></p>
            <p>* This first sentence is in</p>
            <p>Hebrew. This is the best I</p>
            <p>can do with it.<lb/>
                <persName>S. G.</persName></p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>there could read my writing. The cost is the most<lb/> important consideration for me
                at present.<lb/> That is why I expect to go there next week in<lb/> order to talk
                the matter over personally. It is<lb/> possible to say things verbally which cannot
                be<lb/> said in writing.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Also, please let me know who is <persName>Jacob<lb/>
                    Friedman</persName>. He says that he knows me. I,<lb/> however cannot recall
                him. Could he pos-<lb/>sibly be from <placeName>Hamburg</placeName>? Also let
                me<lb/> know whether he can be trusted with holiday<lb/> prayer-books. Expecting
                your immediate<lb/> reply,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Your friend,</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <persName role="author">Jonah Bondi</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Office 429 Broadway</placeName>.</p>
        </body>
